Rules:
SINGLE SHEET GIVING A BRIEF OUTLINE OFTHE WAY TO PLAY

The News from the BBC
The News is quite straightforward to play.  But just to help you in your first few games, here is:-
THE NEWS IN BRIEF

You are dealt 5 News Files and a Briefing Sheet to begin with.  Refer to your Briefing Sheet at all times.
Your Objective is to place 5 News Files on to the News Desk, which correspond to your Briefing Sheet.
You place a News File which corresponds to your Briefing Sheet onto the News Desk by correctly answering a question on that category.
You exchange an unwanted file (ie not on your Breifing sheet) by correctly answering a question from either category shown, before returning it to the bottom of the pack and replacing it with a new File from the top.
Answer Newsflash Questions by using the spinner to select a category.  You  can place a Newsflash File onto the News Desk only when that category is NOT displayed on your Breifing Sheet.
When the Newsflash spinner points to a category already displaayed on your Briefing Sheet you must answer the question, but you cannot file it.  A correct answer, however, enables you to ask ONE other player to remove their file from that category of the News Desk while you must exchange  your newsflash file in the usual way.
OR you may do neither, and retain your Newsflash File for use later in the game.
HOME AND WORLD Files cannot be place onto the Newsd esk .  But you must answer the question correctly in order to exchange these unwanted files.
When you lodge an exclusive file on the News Desk, you remove all opponents' files from the same category.  So pick your time to use it.
And that is the News in Brief.  For a Full round-up, refer to the rules booklet as you play.

BOOKLET- Welcome to the News from the BBC.  The factual, fun filled challenge to your powers of memory, intuition, knowledge and gamesmanship.
...Contains:- 1 News Desk and stands.  1 News Desk header card.  2 News Desk self adhesive player ID Strips, 2 boxes each containing 600 Report Cards (7200 individual reports). 16 Briefing Sheets, 6 Bulletin Boards, 6 News Clips, 1 set of News Files (56 cards), a Flash Board and spinner.

Setting up for play
1.  Slide the two red stands on to the rear of the plastic News Desk
2.  Remove backing strip fro m the two coloured News Desk strips and fix them to the two outside vertical edges of the Desk-in line with the horizontal panels, red on top.,
3.  Slot the News Desk Header Card into position on top of the News Desk.
4.  Position the News Desk accessible to players.
5.  Position the red spinner into the centre of the Newsflash board and lock tight.
6.  position the News Flash board accessible to players.

PLAYING DETAILS AT PRESENT PHOTOCOPIED AND IN GAMES REFERENCE FOLDERS.
